We purified commercial CFP as mentioned above. To prepare AQC/CFP, we immersed the CFP in an ethanolic solution containing 3 mM AQC for 24 h. Subsequently, we dried it at room temperature in air. We estimated the amount of surface-bound AQC using cyclic voltammetric analysis; the surface concentration of AQC (ΓAQC) was estimated using equation (1)1ΓAQCnmolcm−2=Q×n×F×A−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
